<h1>Torsion in Circular Shaft</h1>

<h2>Description</h2>

This project involved an experimental investigation of torsion in circular shafts to study the relationship between applied torque, shear stress, and angle of twist. Experimental results were compared with theoretical calculations to validate torsion equations.

<br />

<h2>Project Objectives</h2>

- Analyze torsional behavior of shafts
- Measure angle of twist
- Calculate shear stress
- Verify torsion theory
- Compare theoretical and experimental results

<h2>Process</h2>

- Set up torsion testing apparatus
- Applied different torque values
- Recorded angle of twist measurements
- Calculated shear stress
- Compared results with theoretical equations
- Documented findings

<h2>Skills Learned</h2>

- Mechanics of Materials
- Torsion Analysis
- Experimental Testing
- Engineering Calculations
- Data Analysis
- Technical Reporting

<h2>Software & Tools Used</h2>

- SOLIDWORKS
- Fusion 360
- Microsoft PowerPoint

<h2>Key Engineering Concepts</h2>

- Shear Stress
- Angle of Twist
- Polar Moment of Inertia
- Torque Transmission
- Torsional Deformation

